Dal 24 aprile al cinema.

Tratto dal primo romanzo di Hunter S. Thompson, The Rum Diary racconta la storia del giornalista free lance Paul Kemp (Johnny Depp). Stanco della confusione e della follia di New York e delle pesanti convenzioni sociali dell'America negli ultimi anni di Eisenhower, Kemp si trasferisce a Puerto Rico per scrivere su un quotidiano locale, The San Juan Star, diretto da Lotterman (Richard Jenkins). Adeguatosi volentieri all'abitudine dell'isola di bere continuamente rum, Paul √® ossessionato da Chenault (Amber Heard), la bellissima americana del Connecticut fidanzata con Sanderson (Aaron Eckhart). Sanderson, un uomo d'affari implicato in loschi investimenti immobiliari, √® uno dei sempre pi√π numerosi imprenditori americani decisi a trasformare l'incontaminata Puerto Rico in un paradiso capitalistico a disposizione dei ricchi. Quando Sanderson lo assume per scrivere a favore del suo progetto, Kemp ha di fronte a s√© una scelta: usare le sue parole per sostenere il corrotto uomo d'affari o usarle per attaccare il suo progetto.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Sexy at MontBlanc Vanity Fair Party in Antonio Berardi
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Sexy at MontBlanc Vanity Fair Party in Antonio Berardi 
http://bit.ly/SubClevverStyle - Subscribe to ClevverStyle!‚Ä®
http://Facebook.com/ClevverStyle - Like Us!‚Ä®‚Ä®

Today's stand out is the stunning Amber Heard at the Montblanc Vanity Fair party in Los Angeles, California. 

The 25 old stunner stepped out in Antonio Berardi frock to celebrate the Collection Princess Grace of Monaco‚Äîwhich is full of beautiful pieces‚Äîanything from jewelry to writing pens. Heard's t-length frock is from the designers 2012 resort collection and I'm actually obsessed. 

It's pretty modest as a whole, but it really has some amazing detailing around the top of the dress‚Äîa crystal pattern to be exact. The frock was tailored perfectly to Amber's fit figure‚Äîtight right about the waist line and hugging her curves. 

Heard paired the gown with none other than Black peep toe Chrisitan Louboutin‚Äîand as for accessories, she kept it simple with delicate Monte Blanc studs. 

The beauty who has played along side studs like Johnny Depp and Eddie Cibrian chose to keep her signature tousled locks and her makeup was a little bit more on the daring side‚Äîwhich is a great compliment to a conservative ensemble‚Äîshe played up her eyes with a winged eyeliner and a dark shadow in the crease of her eye. To round out the look, she lined the bottom of her eye with the same darker color and lined the inner rim of her eyes with a white liner to make them pop! 

Her complexion was glowing and she finishe of the makeup with a very natural pink pout. 

I'm Brianna Baxter for Red.
